        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 8:39PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 839 PM EDT/739 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm over La Porte, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
La Porte, Three Oaks, Shorewood-Tower Hills-Harbert, Dayton, Galien,
Byron, Hudson Lake, Hesston, and Rolling Prarie.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 49 and 61.
Interstate 94 in Michigan between mile markers 9 and 10.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
